recital.p:
Following an application from Probi AB, submitted pursuant to Article 13(5) of Regulation (EC) No 1924/2006, the Authority was required to deliver an opinion on a health claim related to Lactobacillus plantarum 299v (Lp299v) and an increase of non-haem iron absorption (Question No EFSA- Q-2015-00696


                        EFSA Journal 2016;14(7):4550.
                  ). The claim proposed by the applicant was worded as follows: 'Lactobacillus plantarum 299v increases non-haem iron absorption'.
